items.title: Early consumer earnings make the wealth effect clear
items.description: Prominent brands like Coke, 3M, General Motors, and Philip Morris are witnessing a notable strength in consumer spending. However, this strength is not universal. Affluent shoppers are driving economic growth with their spending, whereas consumers on the lower end of the income spectrum are struggling.

items.title: HUL Q2 Preview: Profit may fall 5% YoY as GST transition, weak demand to hit earnings
items.description: Hindustan Unilever is expected to post muted Q2 results, with just 1% revenue growth and a 5% profit decline as GST cuts, extended monsoon, and weak demand hit volumes and margins, though recovery is likely ahead.
